CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 17, 1946, pg. 17, reads: "Frog And Two - Right in groove for Frog Week were these two adorable youngsters, Ira Vann and Lionel Lee Harris, sons of Mr. and Mrs. Charles (Teenie) Harris of Mulford Street. Ira, whose nickname is 'Butch,' is two years old, while his younger brother is just one. - Harris Photo." Ira Vann Harris and Lionel Harris are the sons of Charles "Teenie" Harris and Elsa Harris.
TitMainTitle: Ira Vann Harris holding toy clarinet, standing with his brother Lionel Harris, in yard on either side of frog sculpture, with man squatting on right, at Charles "Teenie" Harris's house, 7604 Mulford Street, Homewood
